<TITLE> 3-day Bangladesh Electronics Fair takes off </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 18 (bdnews24.com)  Import duty on raw materials has been reduced to help domestic industries flourish, the commerce minister said on Thursday. "Hopefully, businesses will tap this scope," Faruque Khan said, while opening a three-day Bangladesh Electronics Fair at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. "The government is helping businesses with better banking facilities and also plans to reduce tax rates," he said, aiming at manufacturers. The fair hosting some 50 electrical goods manufacturers will will be open from 10am through to 8pm everyday. Khan thanked all present for overcoming all problems to carry the electrical goods industry forward. "I hope the power sector will be able to meet your demands in coming days," he said. Bangladesh Electrical Merchandise Manufacturers Association is hosting the fair. BEMMA president Nasim Ullah Hemayet presided over the opening ceremony. bd
